revision.text:
'''倶利伽羅'''、'''倶梨迦羅'''（くりから）は、[[石川県]][[津幡町]]に存在する地名。 *[[倶利迦羅不動寺]] *[[倶利伽羅竜王]] *[[倶利伽羅剣]] *[[倶利伽羅村]] *[[倶利伽羅駅]] *[[道の駅倶利伽羅 源平の郷]] *[[倶利伽羅峠]] *[[倶利伽羅峠の戦い]] *[[倶利伽羅 (漫画家)]]
{{Aimai}}
{{DEFAULTSORT:くりから}} [[Category:日本の地名]]

'''Kurikara''' (倶利伽羅, also written 倶梨迦羅) is the name of a {{ill|dragon king|ja|竜王}}, considered a manifestation of {{ill|Fudō Myōō|ja|不動明王}}, derived from the Sanskrit term "kulihah." It is typically depicted as a black dragon entwined around a sword, known as the {{ill|Kurikara Sword|ja|倶利伽羅剣}}. This image is called the '''Kurikara Dragon King'''.

==Place Name==
Kurikara is also a locality in {{ill|Tsubata, Ishikawa|ja|津幡町}}, Ishikawa Prefecture. It was formerly known as {{ill|Kurikara Village|ja|倶利伽羅村}}, and is now home to the {{ill|Michi-no-Eki Kurikara Genpei no Sato|ja|道の駅倶利伽羅 源平の郷}}.

* In 718 (Yōrō 2), the monk {{ill|Zenmui|ja|善無畏}} is said to have enshrined an image of {{ill|Fudō Myōō|ja|倶利伽羅不動明王}} at what became the {{ill|Kurikara Fudō-ji|ja|倶利伽羅不動寺}}.
* The nearby mountain pass on the border of {{ill|Kaga Province|ja|加賀国}} and {{ill|Etchū Province|ja|越中国}} is known as {{ill|Kurikara Pass|ja|倶利伽羅峠}}. In 1183 (Juei 2), the {{ill|Battle of Kurikara Pass|ja|倶利伽羅峠の戦い}} took place here between the forces of {{ill|Minamoto no Yoshinaka|ja|源義仲}} and the Heike army led by {{ill|Taira no Koremori|ja|平維盛}}. This battle is widely known due to accounts in works like the {{ill|Heike Monogatari|ja|平家物語}}.
* In 1889 (Meiji 22), Kurikara Village was formally established with the enforcement of the town and village system.
* In 1909 (Meiji 42), {{ill|Kurikara Station|ja|倶利伽羅駅}} opened as part of the Hokuriku Main Line.
* In 1957 (Shōwa 32), it was incorporated into Tsubata Town.

===See Also===
* {{ill|Nihongō (spear)|ja|日本号 (槍)}}
* {{ill|Kurikara Tattoos|ja|倶利伽羅紋紋}} – A tattoo design featuring the Kurikara dragon motif, popular since the Edo period, especially among gamblers. It has come to be a common alternate name for tattoos, sometimes abbreviated to "Monmon."
* {{ill|Kurikara (manga artist)|ja|倶利伽羅 (漫画家)}}
* {{ill|Kurikara Pass|ja|倶利伽羅峠}}
* {{ill|Kurikara Fudō-ji|ja|倶利迦羅不動寺}}
* {{ill|Kurikara Sword|ja|倶利伽羅剣}}

{{Disambiguation}}
{{DEFAULTSORT:Kurikara}}

