[[ja:倶利伽羅]]
[[sn:Kurikara Dragon King]]

{{DEFAULTSORT:Kurikara}}

'''Kurikara''' (倶利伽羅, also written 倶梨迦羅) is the name of a {{ill|dragon king|ja|竜王|12=draft}}, considered a manifestation of {{ill|Fudō Myōō|ja|不動明王|1=Acala|lt=Fudō Myōō|2=ja|3=不動明王|12=draft}}, derived from the Sanskrit term "kulihah." It is typically depicted as a black dragon entwined around a sword, known as the {{ill|Kurikara Sword|ja|倶利伽羅剣|12=draft}}. This image is called the '''Kurikara Dragon King'''.

==Place Name==
Kurikara is also a locality in {{ill|Tsubata, Ishikawa|ja|津幡町|12=draft}}, Ishikawa Prefecture. It was formerly known as {{ill|Kurikara Village|ja|倶利伽羅村|12=draft}}, and is now home to the {{ill|Michi-no-Eki Kurikara Genpei no Sato|ja|道の駅倶利伽羅 源平の郷|12=draft}}.

* In 718 (Yōrō 2), the monk {{ill|Zenmui|ja|善無畏|12=draft}} is said to have enshrined an image of {{ill|Fudō Myōō|ja|倶利伽羅不動明王|1=Acala|lt=Fudō Myōō|2=ja|3=不動明王|12=draft}} at what became the {{ill|Kurikara Fudō-ji|ja|倶利伽羅不動寺|12=draft}}.
* The nearby mountain pass on the border of {{ill|Kaga Province|ja|加賀国|12=draft}} and {{ill|Etchū Province|ja|越中国|12=draft}} is known as {{ill|Kurikara Pass|ja|倶利伽羅峠|12=draft}}. In 1183 (Juei 2), the {{ill|Battle of Kurikara Pass|ja|倶利伽羅峠の戦い|12=draft}} took place here between the forces of {{ill|Minamoto no Yoshinaka|ja|源義仲|12=draft}} and the Heike army led by {{ill|Taira no Koremori|ja|平維盛|12=draft}}. This battle is widely known due to accounts in works like the {{ill|Heike Monogatari|ja|平家物語|12=draft}}.
* In 1889 (Meiji 22), Kurikara Village was formally established with the enforcement of the town and village system.
* In 1909 (Meiji 42), {{ill|Kurikara Station|ja|倶利伽羅駅|12=draft}} opened as part of the Hokuriku Main Line.
* In 1957 (Shōwa 32), it was incorporated into Tsubata Town.

===See Also===
* {{ill|Nihongō (spear)|ja|日本号 (槍)|12=draft}}
* {{ill|Kurikara Tattoos|ja|倶利伽羅紋紋|12=draft}} – A tattoo design featuring the Kurikara dragon motif, popular since the Edo period, especially among gamblers. It has come to be a common alternate name for tattoos, sometimes abbreviated to "Monmon."
* {{ill|Kurikara (manga artist)|ja|倶利伽羅 (漫画家)|12=draft}}
* {{ill|Kurikara Pass|ja|倶利伽羅峠|12=draft}}
* {{ill|Kurikara Fudō-ji|ja|倶利迦羅不動寺|12=draft}}
* {{ill|Kurikara Sword|ja|倶利伽羅剣|12=draft}}

