Kurikara is also a locality in [[:en:Tsubata, Ishikawa|Tsubata, Ishikawa]], Ishikawa Prefecture. It was formerly known as {{ill|Kurikara Village|ja|倶利伽羅村|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kurikara Village|qq=}}, and is now home to the {{ill|Michi-no-Eki Kurikara Genpei no Sato|ja|道の駅倶利伽羅 源平の郷|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Michi-no-Eki Kurikara Genpei no Sato|qq=}}.

* In 718 (Yōrō 2), the monk [[:en:Śubhakarasiṃha|Zenmui]] is said to have enshrined an image of [[:en:Acala|Fudō Myōō]] at what became the {{ill|Kurikara Fudō-ji|ja|倶利伽羅不動寺|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kurikara Fudō-ji|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 倶利迦羅不動寺}}.
* The nearby mountain pass on the border of [[:en:Kaga Province|Kaga Province]] and [[:en:Etchū Province|Etchū Province]] is known as {{ill|Kurikara Pass|ja|倶利伽羅峠|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kurikara Pass|qq=}}. In 1183 (Juei 2), the [[:en:Battle of Kurikara Pass|Battle of Kurikara Pass]] took place here between the forces of [[:en:Minamoto no Yoshinaka|Minamoto no Yoshinaka]] and the Heike army led by [[:en:Taira no Koremori|Taira no Koremori]]. This battle is widely known due to accounts in works like the [[:en:The Tale of the Heike|Heike Monogatari]].
* In 1889 (Meiji 22), Kurikara Village was formally established with the enforcement of the town and village system.
* In 1909 (Meiji 42), [[:en:Kurikara Station|Kurikara Station]] opened as part of the Hokuriku Main Line.
* In 1957 (Shōwa 32), it was incorporated into Tsubata Town.

===See Also===
* {{ill|Nihongō (spear)|ja|日本号 (槍)|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nihongō (spear)|qq=}}
* {{ill|Kurikara Tattoos|ja|倶利伽羅紋紋|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kurikara Tattoos|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} – A tattoo design featuring the Kurikara dragon motif, popular since the Edo period, especially among gamblers. It has come to be a common alternate name for tattoos, sometimes abbreviated to "Monmon."
* {{ill|Kurikara (manga artist)|ja|倶利伽羅 (漫画家)|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kurikara (manga artist)|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}
* {{ill|Kurikara Pass|ja|倶利伽羅峠|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kurikara Pass|qq=}}
* {{ill|Kurikara Fudō-ji|ja|倶利迦羅不動寺|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kurikara Fudō-ji|qq=}}
* {{ill|Kurikara Sword|ja|倶利伽羅剣|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kurikara Sword|qq=}}

